{"word":"μειόω","slug":"μειόω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μειόω</b></el> <el>(μειόω,) ( φυτ. <el>-ώσω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μείων'><el>μείων</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to make smaller, to lessen, moderate</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to lessen in honour, degrade</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to lessen by word, extenuate, disparage</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to become worse</i> or <i>weaker</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to fall short of</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}